
[1]pacify

   PACIFY, v.t. [L., peace, and to make.]

   1. To appease, as wrath or other violent passion or appetite; to calm;
   to still; to quiet; to allay agitation or excitement; as, to pacify a
   man when angry, or to pacify his wrath or rage; the word being applied
   both to the person and to the passion. So we say, to pacify hunger, to
   pacify importunate demands.

   2. To restore peace to; to tranquilize; as, to pacify countries in
   contention.
